body:
Support was added for finding unpacked arrays via the VPI, however this did not include support for getting the ranges of the arrays. This lack of functionality is causing cocotb runs to fail.

Per IEEE 1800-2017 37.11:

> vpi_iterate(vpiRange, instance_array_handle) shall return the set of instance array ranges beginning with the
leftmost range of the array declaration and iterating through the rightmost range. Using the vpiLeftRange/
vpiRightRange properties returns the bounds of the leftmost dimension of a multidimensional array.

For example, to get the range of the outermost dimension of an unpacked array the following code would be correct.
```c
vpiHandle iter = vpi_iterate(vpiRange, hdl);
assert(iter != NULL);
vpiHandle rangeHdl = vpi_scan(iter);
assert(rangeHdl != NULL);
int leftBound = vpi_get(vpiLeftRange, rangeHdl);
int rightBound = vpi_get(vpiRightRange, rangeHdl);
vpi_release_handle(rangeHdl);  // optional, but shouldn't error
vpi_release_handle(iter);  // ends iterator early, *required*
```

